# Flutter Widget/Build Guardrails

Mandatory rules for all UI code. Full detail in `.github/copilot-instructions.md`.

## Never create functions that return widgets

```dart
// ❌ WRONG
Widget _buildHeader() => Container(...);

// ✅ CORRECT
class HeaderWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  const HeaderWidget({super.key});
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) => Container(...);
}
```

Always widget classes with `const` constructors — including wrapper/filter
helpers (`Widget _filtered(Widget child)` → a widget class taking `child`).

## Never declare variables or run logic inside build()

Class fields / constructor params instead. Only context reads used in the
returned tree are allowed inside `build` (`Theme.of(context)`,
`context.colorScheme`, `context.width`), plus `LayoutBuilder` constraints in
their own callback.

## Never compute data inside builder callbacks

`itemBuilder`, `BlocBuilder.builder`, `ValueListenableBuilder.builder`, etc. take
inline expressions only. Pre-compute sorted/filtered data in the Bloc state or a
`ValueNotifier` (see `LibraryBloc._pipeline`).

## Never use setState

`ValueNotifier` + `ValueListenableBuilder` / `ListenableBuilder` for local state;
Bloc for feature state.

## Never use double.infinity for sizing

Use `context.width` / `context.height`.

## All sizes go through flutter_screenutil

`16.w`, `16.h`, `12.r`, `12.sp`, `16.verticalSpace`. Banned raw literals:
`SizedBox(height: 16)`, `EdgeInsets.all(12)`, `BorderRadius.circular(12)`,
`fontSize: 12`. Permitted unscaled: `0`, hairline `1`, and non-length integers
(`maxLines: 1`, `Duration(...)`). Converting a literal to `.h`/`.w`/`.r`/`.sp`
drops `const` and needs
`import 'package:flutter_screenutil/flutter_screenutil.dart';`.
